            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>ucius</ex></expan> Gaviarius <expan><abbr>L</abbr><ex>uci</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>T</abbr><ex>iti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>n</abbr><ex>epos</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>aug</abbr><ex>ur</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>C</abbr><ex>aius</ex></expan> <supplied reason="lost">Iuliu</supplied>s <lb n="2"/>Caesaris <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibertus</ex></expan> Meges IIviri qu<expan><ex>in</ex><abbr>que</abbr><ex>nnales</ex></expan> por<supplied reason="lost">tam</supplied> <lb n="3"/>et turrim ex <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ecreto</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ecurionum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>e</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>ecunia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>ublica</ex></expan> reficiu<supplied reason="lost">ndas</supplied> <lb n="4"/>coeraverunt eidemque pr<supplied reason="lost">o</supplied><lb break="no" n="5"/>baverunt constat HS ||<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">|(trium milium)?D</supplied>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Weitere Inschrift von Gaviarius und Meges: AE 1982, 766. Z. 5 (Ende): hinter HS zwei Zahlzeichen für je 1000; ein drittes Zeichen für 1000 und ein D ergänzt von Prendi.</p>
            </div>
